        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Niu Yawei",
          "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-02-12 07:33:10.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "subject": "LU-3919 lvfs: fid2dentry violates locking order",
        "message": "LU-3919 lvfs: fid2dentry violates locking order\n\nThe proper locking order should be i_mutex -> journal_lock, however,\nin most case we call mds/mgs_fid2dentry() (which acquires i_mutex\nfor iopen dir) after journal started, that violates the locking\norder and will cause deadlock in certain situation.\n\nActually it's not necessary to hold the i_mutex of iopen dir when\nperforming fid2dentry. This patch skips the i_mutex locking for\nthat case to avoid the locking order violation.\n\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <yawei.niu@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I7a325131c79f20cc908b035e9e35d3041bd68aec\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
